---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import DataDisclaimer from '../components/DataDisclaimer.astro';
import AdSlot from '../components/AdSlot.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Data Methodology & Calculation Rules — World Companies by Market Cap"
  description="Learn how market capitalization, earnings, revenue, financial ratios, currency conversions, and stock price changes are calculated and updated."
>
  <DataDisclaimer />

  <div class="max-w-[1000px] mx-auto px-4 py-12 space-y-10">
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-blue-500/10 text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 text-xs font-semibold">
        <span>📖 Data Standard</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>Methodology & Disclosures</span>
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">
        Data Methodology & Calculation Architecture
      </h1>
      <p class="text-base text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        World Companies by Market Cap aggregates market capitalization, equity valuation metrics, balance sheet statements, and employee metrics across major global stock exchanges.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">1. Market Capitalization Calculation</h2>
        <p>
          Market Capitalization is computed continuously by multiplying total outstanding common shares by the current market price per share in local currency, converted into USD at real-time spot foreign exchange rates.
        </p>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-[var(--color-bg-alt)] border border-[var(--color-border)] font-mono text-xs text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">
          Market Cap = Total Outstanding Shares × Current Share Price (USD Converted)
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">2. Currency Conversions</h2>
        <p>
          Primary market prices listed in non-USD foreign currencies (e.g. EUR, JPY, GBP, INR, CAD, KRW, CHF, HKD, SAR) are converted dynamically into USD, EUR, GBP, JPY, CAD, INR, or AUD using daily interbank exchange rates.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">3. Valuation Ratios & Metrics</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>P/E Ratio (Price-to-Earnings):</strong> Current Market Price divided by Diluted Trailing Twelve Months (TTM) Net Income Per Share.</li>
          <li><strong>Price-to-Book (P/B):</strong> Total Market Capitalization divided by Total Net Assets (Equity Shareholders' Equity).</li>
          <li><strong>Operating Margin:</strong> Operating Income (EBIT) divided by TTM Total Revenue, expressed as a percentage.</li>
          <li><strong>Dividend Yield:</strong> Total annualized dividend payout per share divided by the current share price.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">4. Sector Classification Standard</h2>
        <p>
          Companies are categorized into 11 primary sectors based on the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS): Technology, Consumer Cyclical, Financial Services, Communication Services, Healthcare, Energy, Industrials, Consumer Defensive, Basic Materials, Utilities, and Real Estate.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <AdSlot variant="banner" />
  </div>
</Layout>
